===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{senseid|en|Q568}}{{lb|en|uncountable}} The simplest [[alkali]] [[metal]], the lightest solid element, and the third lightest chemical element (''symbol'' Li) with an [[atomic number]] of 3.
#* '''2019''', George Monbiot, ''[https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2019/mar/07/cars-killing-us-driving-environment-phase-out Cars are killing us. Within 10 years, we must phase them out]'' in the Guardian.
#*: Already, beautiful places are being wrecked by an electric vehicle resource rush. '''Lithium''' mining, for example, is now poisoning rivers and depleting groundwater from Tibet to Bolivia.
# {{lb|en|pharmaceutical drug|uncountable}} [[lithium carbonate|Lithium carbonate]] or other preparations of lithium metal used to treat [[manic depression]] and [[bipolar disorder]]s.
# A [[lithium battery]].

